title: 1952 Noir- Loan Shark - He knew every racket's strength... and every woman's weakness!

sources.title: 1952 Noir- Loan Shark - He knew every racket's strength... and every woman's weakness!
sources.description:
Ex-con Joe Gargan, takes on a high-stakes mission to expose an usury, and squeezing his old friends dry. With fists flying and secrets unraveling, Joe must outsmart the slick and sinister Lou Donelli before the city's underworld swallows him whole.

Loan Shark is a 1952 American crime film noir directed by Seymour Friedman.

Main Actors:
George Raft - Joe Gargen
Dorothy Hart - Ann Nelson
Paul Stewart - Lou Donelli
John Hoyt - Vince Phillips
Helen Westcott - Martha Gargen Haines
Henry Slate - Paul Nelson
Russell Johnson - Charlie Thompson
Margia Dean - Ivy
Benny Baker - Tubby
Lawrence Dobkin - Walter Kerr
Virginia Carroll - Netta Casmer
Robert Bice - Steve Casmer
George Eldredge - Mr. Howell
Ross Elliott - Norm
William Tannen - Rourke
Harlan Warde - Lt. White
Robert B. Williams - Scully
Charles Meredith - F.L. Rennick
William Edward Phipps - Ed Haines
Barbara Woodell - Mrs. Hilton
Robert Karnes - Police Lieutenant
